<LP>
   MILAN -- The Ferruzzi Group subsidiary Montedison S.p.A.
said that it has acquired Hercules Inc.'s 50% interest in
their equally owned venture, Moplefan SPA. Terms of the
transaction weren't disclosed.
   Moplefan, a European producer of polypropylene staple,
yarn and film, currently has total production capacity of
120,000 tons per year.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Moplefan's 1989 revenue was about 320 billion lire ($264
million). The company employs 1,750.
</TEXT>
